OL,3,CWelfare cuts rebellion - is your MP
OL,4,Cpart of the group opposing the
OL,5,Cgovernment?
OL,7,FAfter months of various groups of
OL,8,Fbackbench Labour MPs expressing their
OL,9,Fconcerns about the welfare cuts to the
OL,10,Fgovernment and in the media, this week
OL,11,F126 have come together to back an
OL,12,Famendment that would halt the
OL,13,Flegislation in its tracks.
OL,15,FThe "reasoned amendment" to the bill,
OL,16,Fwhich would see key disability and
OL,17,Fhealth benefits slashed for millions
OL,18,Fof people, has attracted more and more
OL,19,Fnames since it was first tabled on
OL,20,FMonday.
