OL,4,Cpart of the group opposing the
OL,5,Cgovernment?
OL,7,FSir Keir Starmer told MPs on Thursday:
OL,8,F"We want to see reform implemented
OL,9,Fwith Labour values of fairness.
OL,11,F"That conversation will continue in
OL,12,Fthe coming days, so we can begin
OL,13,Fmaking change together on Tuesday."
OL,15,FOnly 24 hours before, the PM dismissed
OL,16,Fthe rebels as "noises off".
OL,18,FIf all opposition parties vote against
OL,19,Fthe bill, only 83 Labour MPs need to
OL,20,Fjoin them for it to be defeated.
